<div class="container page-content py-5">

  <div class="vpadding-thick">
    <%= image_tag "hiking/joshua-tree-banner.jpg", alt: "Panoramic view of Joshua Tree National Park at sunset with dramatic orange clouds, rock formations, and desert vegetation", class: "hiking-banner" %>
    <p class="caption text-end w-100">Joshua Tree National Park, California</p>
  </div>

  <div class="pt-5">
    <h1 class="sage"><em>Hiking</em></h1>
  </div>

  <div class="py-4">
    <p>
      I have always been passionate about spending time in nature, and hiking has been my favorite way to experience its beauty. It wakes up my senses, grounds me, and instills in me a deep appreciation for silence—something that is sorely underrated in our society. As I do with most things I enjoy, I set goals for myself in this hobby. Although I have my hiking ambitions, I try to remain cognizant that this is about the journey, not the destination.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="row vpadding-thin text-start">
    <div class="col-3">
      <h3 class="sage"><em>AllTrails</em></h3>
    </div>
    <div class="col-9">
      <p>
        I've logged the bulk of my outdoor adventures on <a class="external-link link-offset-2 link-offset-3-hover link-underline link-underline-opacity-0 link-underline-opacity-75-hover" href="https://www.alltrails.com/members/wilson-cunningham" target="_blank">AllTrails</a>. 
        To see what I've been up to on the trails, check out my 
        <a class="external-link link-offset-2 link-offset-3-hover link-underline link-underline-opacity-0 link-underline-opacity-75-hover" href="https://www.alltrails.com/members/wilson-cunningham" target="_blank">profile</a>. 
        Also, I am <em>always</em> looking for new trails and camping spots. If you have any recommendations, please reach out!
      </p>
    </div>

